Not eliminate it but to reduce the chance of a successful double attack on backstab to a lower percent chance of that happening.<br>
In all honestly i don't think pre50 we do substatially more damage then monks ect..unless your twinked and well twinks don't garner balance in the firstplace.<br>
<br>
It really isn't till 55 that we make that major jump ahead of others in the damage department and its mostly due to DoubleBackstabs, so lowering the successrate of doubleBackstabs would lower our damage output at highlevels without removing any skills and would have no effect on the class pre55 which i really think is perfectly balanced.<br>
<br>
If our damage output is part of the reason that evade is beign so severly looked at than i would suggest considering this idea as well or instead of crippling evade.<br>
This would only affect the 55+ crowd and it would easily be controllable..ie if you reduce the success rate of DBS to 50% you on average would lower our damage output at 60 by 15%..ect ect..<br>
I guess i'm suggesting this as an idea that IF part of the reasoning for the severity of the changes to evade are because of large raids at highlevels..i'd rather our role at that point be adjusted rather then the whole class thru all levels.<br>
I might be way off base and some people might think i'm insane for suggesting it..but if on the off chance kendrick might still be following this thread..hope it helps determine where the real unbalanceing of the class is.<br>
