<br>
The generalization that dropping you to 2nd on the list is not good enough because it will soon be on you again and you are dead if Evade is not available?  Utter nonsense.  How long does Hide take to refresh?  Are you THAT feeble that you can't survive a few seconds of being attacked?  A rogue is a melee character for @#%$ sakes.  Act like it.<br>
<br>
I'm so tired of &quot;a rogue's JOB is to do damage, a warriors JOB is to take it, a cleric JOB is to CH the main tank only, blah blah blah&quot;...are you playing a game or working on an assembly line?  Use a little creativity, a little ingeniuity for once.<br>
<br>
Deal with it.  I prefer a percentage reduction to a fixed place on the list, it makes more sense.  But you know what?  Either way I will figure out a way to deal with it and make it work.  End of story.  @#%$ people, what's so bad about the notion that you may have to THINK a little, be a little creative in fighting instead of the cookie cutter, &quot;attack, evade, keep mob on main tank, cleric CH's main tank&quot;, repeated button pushing for hours?<br>
<br>
A good player is made by their ability to think and make a situation work, not pre-determined by the skill set Verant provides.<br>
<br>
As a side note, the more impacting and unnecessary change here is greying out ID when a special attack is used and vice versa.  Using a little skill, I time ID's to proc precisely after backstab ungreys.  This change will delay that - I won't be able to press ID and start the 5 second ID process until AFTER backstab ungreys now.  It makes it easier to see grey buttons for simpletons who can't figure out the timing, but removes the skill required to maximize your ID attempts with the most chance for success.  gee, big thanks to the person who needlessly brought up this suggestion.  This is more of a nerf than anything to do with evade.<br>
