</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugeffindagrifter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geffin Dagrifter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 11:30:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> The original description of the hate list given by Kendrick said that when a player first gets on the list, their hate value is 128 and a rogue that successfully evades drops to 120.<br>
<br>
The problem was described as: with the new larger hate lists, the rogue ends up below people on the other side of the zone who just happen to be on the hate list without ever having attacked.<br>
<br>
Why not just change the constant value up a bit to be something like 128 + the amount of hate generated by a single normal hit? We could then evade to the bottom of the attackers on the hate list, but still not be able to evade onto any other player that was never engaged in the battle.<br>
<br>
It also seems to me that introducing a new formula and the code to implement it would be more error-prone than just adjusting the constant hate factor constant that is already in the code. So, not only does the new suggestion seem <b>extremely</b> more deadly to the rogue by design, it is likely the implementation will be goofed up as well. <p><img src="http://members.home.com/lyndib/signatures/Geffin_Signature.gif" width="350" height="100">
