<br>
<br>
Also, for the people talking about how taunt will offset this; taunt (as I have understood it) on a successful skill check, puts you one (1) point higher than the #1 person on the hate list. Doesn't increase your rate of hate accumulation, doesn't _keep_ you there until taunt recycles, and it has the same recycle time as hide. If a warrior can't taunt off of me now, how is he going to after a succesful evade only puts me halfway between him and cleric?<br>
<br>
We've been given the tools to outdamage other classes handily, yet still keep the mob off of us. I agree that dropping completely off the hate list is overpowered, however staying at the top unless we stand around with our hands at our sides (or die) is too far in the other direction. I like Wendolyn's random idea, puts some excitement and unpredictability back in the game. <p>Dalarian Silvershade <semi retired><BR>
