~Unfortunately~</i> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uragathor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ragathor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/01 12:04:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> I played my rogue for many months pre-evade, and nearly quit EQ as a result. I have 4 issues:<br>
<br>
#1:  Taunt doesn't work well enough to save a rogue.If a tank taunts his way to the top of the hate list, the rogue is going to be back to the top in a split second - within one or two hits. It's not like we're casters who have 6-second recast times, and give the warrior time to continue building up hate.<br>
<br>
#2: Evade is about DEALING DAMAGE, not just escaping aggro. This is about rogues getting their damage-dealing potential nerfed. When we get the aggro, we can't do backstab, and our damage-dealing potential drops by around 33%. We're left doing less damage than monks. We're basically warriors without the hitpoints and AC.<br>
<br>
THIS was the situation pre-evade. I'm really afraid that the &quot;taking responsibility for our damage&quot; is going to amount to the same thing. It means our damage-dealing potential is going down... either by choice (we ease off on doing damage), or by being forced into it (The mob starts tearing us a new one, both increasing our risk AND massively reducing our damage output).<br>
<br>
The reason for evade's very existance from the beginning was to allow us to live up to our potential, and have a CHANCE of significantly outdamaging the other high-damage melee classes. People have lost sight of that, thinking of it more as a &quot;get out of jail free card&quot;. <br>
<br>
<br>
#3: I really fear the proposed implementation is insufficient. I really wish they'd rethink it. I think the example Kendrick provided is not a close enough representation of hate list distribution in a multi-group environment.  I think the hate values for the top 3 or 4 people are much more tightly distributed ... I fear that a successful evade (ASSUMING success... Evade is notorious for NOT working when you need it most) will drop a rogue much LESS than 10% of their hate value in many situations.<br>
<br>
#4: I also think 10% is inadequate - it basically puts a cap on our damage at no more than 10% of the damage output of any other person in our group. In a SMALL GROUP situation (moving away from the raid mentality for a moment), this is reall, really bad. Particularly if the group's tank is, say, a paladin. <br>
<br>
PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE re-think this implementation. In the past, evade FUNCTIONALLY dropped us to about the sixth place on the hate list... a position that we were still able to climb out of pretty quickly in a single-group situation. Would it be so horrible to have it continue to do so with expanded hatelist? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessageRange?topicID=2059.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessageRange?topicID=2059.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessageRange?topicID=2059.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessageRange?topicID=2059.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessageRange?topicID=2059.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessageRange?topicID=2059.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a> <b>7</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessageRange?topicID=2059.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessageRange?topicID=2059.topic&start=161&stop=167>9</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessage?topicID=2067.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showMessage?topicID=2061.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc